The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The State Bank of India and ICICI Bank today hiked their lending rates by 50 basis points, which will make existing home, auto and commercial loans expensive. The SBI also hiked its deposit rates by up to 150 basis points for various maturities. ICICI Bank revised its benchmark prime lending rate to 16.25 per cent from 15.75 per cent at present.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Inflation for July slid back in single digit to 9.97 per cent after a gap of five months, on account of moderating food and non-food prices. The inflation based on wholesale prices declined 0.58 per cent last month from 10.55 per cent in June.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The Insurance Regulatory and Development Authority has asked insurance companies not to provide fabricated sense of security through advertisements to allure customers towards Ulips and other schemes.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: BlackBerry mobile phone maker Research In Motion (RIM) has agreed to provide security agencies partial access to its messenger services by September 1 and will complete the project by the end of the year.                                                                                                                          
